!!!
%html
  %head
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="/css/global.css")
    %script{:src => "https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.1/jquery.min.js"}
    %script{:src => "https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.8.16/jquery-ui.min.js"}
    %script{:src => "/js/ui.js"}
    %script{:src => "/js/processing.min.js"} 

    %title Engagement Browser

  %body
    %canvas#neoviz
    %header
      %section#title
        %h1 Harding Point
        %p Engagement Browser
      %section#search
        %form{:action => "/", :method => "get"}
          %label Node ID:
          %input#neoid{:type => "text", :value => "#{@neoid}", :name => "neoid"}
          %input#loadnode{:type => "submit", :value => "Load", :class => "button"}
      %br{:style => "clear: both;"}
    %section#content
      = yield
    %aside
      %div#explanation
        / Engagement Browser introduction
        %h2 About
        %p
          Engagement Browser is an attempt to visually navigate through
          %a{:href => "http://neo4j.org"} Neo4j 
          by using the 
          %a{:href => "https://github.com/maxdemarzi/neography"} Neography
          Gem.

          It takes advantage of the latest HTML5 features
          by using the canvas element for drawing.
        %h3 Code          
        %p
          Available at
          %a{:href => "https://github.com/HardingPoint/EngagementBrowser.git", :target => "_blank"} Engagement Browser Github

      <div id="browser_not_supported">
      Your Browser is currently not supported.<br/><br/>Try one of these:<br/>
      <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/firefox.html">Firefox 3.6</a><br/>
      <a href="http://www.apple.com/safari/">Safari 4.0</a><br/>
      <a href="http://www.google.com/chrome/">Chrome</a><br/>
      </div>
